
---


@startuml

' Define classes with attributes and methods

class Cinema {
    - id: String
    - name: String
    - town: String
    + addTheatre(Theatre): void
    + getAvailableCopies(Movie): List<MovieCopy>
}

class Theatre {
    - id: String
    - cinemaId: String
    - name: String
    - capacity: int
    + getAvailableSeats(): int
}

class Movie {
    - id: String
    - title: String
    - duration: int
    - releaseDate: Date
}

class MovieCopy {
    - id: String
    - movieId: String
    - cinemaId: String
    - status: CopyStatus
    + move(Cinema): boolean
}

enum CopyStatus {
    AVAILABLE
    IN_USE
    OUT_OF_SERVICE
}

class Show {
    - id: String
    - movieCopyId: String
    - theatreId: String
    - startTime: DateTime
    - endTime: DateTime
    - published: boolean
    + publish(): void
    + cancel(): boolean
    + offerAlternativeSeat(Reservation): boolean
}

class Reservation {
    - id: String
    - showId: String
    - customerId: String
    - seatsReserved: List<Seat>
    - paymentMethod: PaymentMethod
    - reservationTime: DateTime
    - status: ReservationStatus
    + cancel(): boolean
    + debitCreditCard(): boolean
}

enum ReservationStatus {
    PENDING
    CONFIRMED
    CANCELLED
    EXPIRED
}

enum PaymentMethod {
    CREDIT_CARD
}

class Seat {
    - id: String
    - theatreId: String
    - row: int
    - number: int
    - isReserved: boolean
}

class Ticket {
    - id: String
    - showId: String
    - seatId: String
    - customerName: String (optional)
    - issuedAt: DateTime
    - type: TicketType
}

enum TicketType {
    ONLINE_RESERVATION
    ON_SITE_PURCHASE
}

class Customer {
    - id: String
    - name: String
    - email: String
    - creditCardInfo: String
}

' Relationships

Cinema "1" *-- "many" Theatre : contains
Cinema "1" *-- "many" MovieCopy : owns
Movie "1" *-- "many" MovieCopy : has copies
Theatre "1" *-- "many" Show : hosts
Show "1" *-- "1" MovieCopy : uses copy
Show "1" *-- "many" Reservation : has reservations
Show "1" *-- "many" Ticket : has tickets
Reservation "1" *-- "many" Seat : reserves
Theatre "1" *-- "many" Seat : has seats
Customer "1" *-- "many" Reservation : makes
Customer "0..*" -- "many" Ticket : purchases
Ticket "1" *-- "1" Seat : assigned to

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- `MovieCopy` is tied to a specific `Cinema` and can be moved between cinemas.
- A `Show` is scheduled in a `Theatre` using a specific `MovieCopy`.
- `Reservations` are linked to a `Customer`, whereas `Tickets` bought at the entrance may not be.
- The `Reservation` class includes cancellation and refund logic.
- `Offering an alternative seat` is modeled as a method of the `Show` class.
- The system supports online and on-site ticket purchasing with different rules.

